# Part I: Requirements

## 1. Business Requirements

### 1.1 Problem Statement

Modern applications generate vast amounts of observability data (metrics, logs, traces), but analyzing this data to identify root causes and determine actionable solutions remains time-consuming and requires significant expertise. Teams face:

- **Reactive Operations:** Issues are discovered only after they impact users
- **Alert Fatigue:** Too many alerts without context or priority
- **Slow Incident Resolution:** Hours spent correlating metrics, logs, and code changes
- **Knowledge Silos:** Only senior engineers can effectively diagnose complex issues
- **Missed Opportunities:** Performance optimizations and cost savings go unnoticed

### 1.2 Business Objectives

| ID | Objective | Target Metric |
|----|-----------|---------------|
| BO-1 | Reduce mean time to resolution (MTTR) for incidents | 50% reduction |
| BO-2 | Enable proactive issue detection before user impact | 70% of issues detected proactively |
| BO-3 | Democratize system analysis across engineering team | All engineers can interpret system health |
| BO-4 | Reduce infrastructure costs through optimization | Identify $500+/month in savings |
| BO-5 | Decrease manual monitoring time | Save 10+ hours/week per team |

### 1.3 Success Criteria

The system is considered successful if it:

1. **Accuracy:** Provides correct root cause analysis in >85% of cases
2. **Actionability:** Generates implementable recommendations for >90% of identified issues
3. **Speed:** Completes analysis within 3 minutes (P95)
4. **Adoption:** Used regularly by >80% of engineering team
5. **Impact:** Measurably improves system reliability and reduces costs

---

## 2. Functional Requirements

### 2.1 Core Capabilities

#### FR-1: Data Collection & Aggregation

**Requirement:** The system SHALL collect observability data from New Relic and source code context from GitHub.

**Details:**
- **FR-1.1:** Collect APM metrics (response time, throughput, error rate, Apdex score)
- **FR-1.2:** Collect error traces with full stack traces
- **FR-1.3:** Collect transaction traces showing slow operations
- **FR-1.4:** Collect infrastructure metrics (CPU, memory, disk, network)
- **FR-1.5:** Collect application logs with filtering capability
- **FR-1.6:** Retrieve source code files from GitHub repositories
- **FR-1.7:** Retrieve recent commit history and changes
- **FR-1.8:** Support configurable time ranges for data collection
- **FR-1.9:** Handle rate limits and implement retry logic
- **FR-1.10:** Normalize data from different sources into unified format

**Priority:** P0 (Critical)  
**Dependencies:** New Relic API access, GitHub API access

#### FR-2: Health Assessment

**Requirement:** The system SHALL calculate an overall health score for monitored applications.

**Details:**
- **FR-2.1:** Calculate health score on 0-10 scale based on multiple factors:
  - Performance metrics (30% weight)
  - Reliability/error rate (30% weight)
  - Resource efficiency (20% weight)
  - User satisfaction/Apdex (20% weight)
- **FR-2.2:** Classify system status as: Healthy (8-10), Warning (6-8), Critical (<6)
- **FR-2.3:** Compare current metrics against historical baseline
- **FR-2.4:** Detect anomalies and deviations from normal behavior
- **FR-2.5:** Provide health score trends over time

**Priority:** P0 (Critical)

#### FR-3: Issue Detection & Analysis

**Requirement:** The system SHALL automatically detect issues and perform root cause analysis.

**Details:**
- **FR-3.1:** Detect performance degradations (response time, throughput)
- **FR-3.2:** Identify error patterns and spikes
- **FR-3.3:** Detect resource utilization issues
- **FR-3.4:** Identify database query problems (N+1, slow queries)
- **FR-3.5:** Detect memory leaks through trend analysis
- **FR-3.6:** Correlate issues with recent code deployments
- **FR-3.7:** Link error stack traces to specific source code lines
- **FR-3.8:** Determine root causes using AI analysis
- **FR-3.9:** Assess impact of each issue (users affected, severity)
- **FR-3.10:** Classify issues by category (performance, error, infrastructure, cost)

**Priority:** P0 (Critical)

#### FR-4: AI-Powered Analysis

**Requirement:** The system SHALL use AI/LLM to analyze issues with full context.

**Details:**
- **FR-4.1:** Build comprehensive context combining metrics, logs, traces, and code
- **FR-4.2:** Provide relevant code snippets to AI for analysis
- **FR-4.3:** Include recent commit history in analysis context
- **FR-4.4:** Use structured prompts for consistent analysis
- **FR-4.5:** Support multi-stage analysis (quick scan → deep dive)
- **FR-4.6:** Validate AI recommendations for feasibility
- **FR-4.7:** Maintain conversation history for follow-up analysis
- **FR-4.8:** Support different AI models (GPT-4, GPT-4o)

**Priority:** P0 (Critical)  
**Dependencies:** OpenAI API or equivalent

#### FR-5: Recommendation Generation

**Requirement:** The system SHALL generate actionable recommendations to fix identified issues.

**Details:**
- **FR-5.1:** Generate specific code fixes with line numbers
- **FR-5.2:** Provide before/after code comparisons (diffs)
- **FR-5.3:** Suggest configuration changes with expected impact
- **FR-5.4:** Recommend infrastructure adjustments
- **FR-5.5:** Provide implementation steps for each recommendation
- **FR-5.6:** Include confidence scores for recommendations
- **FR-5.7:** Explain why each recommendation will help
- **FR-5.8:** Prioritize recommendations by impact and urgency
- **FR-5.9:** Suggest preventive measures to avoid recurrence

**Priority:** P0 (Critical)

#### FR-6: Reporting & Notification

**Requirement:** The system SHALL generate reports and send notifications to appropriate channels.

**Details:**
- **FR-6.1:** Generate structured JSON reports with full analysis
- **FR-6.2:** Generate human-readable Markdown reports
- **FR-6.3:** Send alerts to Slack channels
- **FR-6.4:** Support email notifications
- **FR-6.5:** Include severity-based alert routing
- **FR-6.6:** Provide report history and archival
- **FR-6.7:** Support custom notification templates
- **FR-6.8:** Include actionable links in notifications

**Priority:** P1 (High)

#### FR-7: Multiple Execution Modes

**Requirement:** The system SHALL support multiple modes of operation.

**Details:**
- **FR-7.1:** On-demand analysis via CLI
- **FR-7.2:** Scheduled periodic analysis
- **FR-7.3:** Event-driven analysis triggered by external events
- **FR-7.4:** Continuous monitoring mode
- **FR-7.5:** Post-deployment verification mode
- **FR-7.6:** Ad-hoc investigation mode with custom parameters

**Priority:** P1 (High)

#### FR-8: Cost Optimization Analysis

**Requirement:** The system SHALL identify opportunities for cost optimization.

**Details:**
- **FR-8.1:** Analyze resource utilization patterns
- **FR-8.2:** Identify oversized infrastructure resources
- **FR-8.3:** Detect inefficient database queries
- **FR-8.4:** Suggest caching opportunities
- **FR-8.5:** Estimate cost savings for each recommendation
- **FR-8.6:** Analyze trends to predict future resource needs

**Priority:** P2 (Medium)

### 2.2 Interface Requirements

#### FR-9: Command Line Interface

**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a comprehensive CLI.

**Details:**
- **FR-9.1:** Support analysis commands with configurable parameters
- **FR-9.2:** Provide status and progress feedback
- **FR-9.3:** Support output formatting options (JSON, Markdown, plain text)
- **FR-9.4:** Enable configuration management via CLI
- **FR-9.5:** Provide help and documentation
- **FR-9.6:** Support piping and scripting integration

**Priority:** P0 (Critical)

#### FR-10: REST API (Optional Phase 1)

**Requirement:** The system MAY provide a REST API for programmatic access.

**Details:**
- **FR-10.1:** Trigger analysis via POST endpoint
- **FR-10.2:** Query analysis status and results
- **FR-10.3:** Retrieve application health scores
- **FR-10.4:** Access historical reports
- **FR-10.5:** Support webhook callbacks for async operations
- **FR-10.6:** Provide API authentication and authorization

**Priority:** P2 (Medium) - Optional for Phase 1

### 2.3 Configuration Requirements

#### FR-11: Configuration Management

**Requirement:** The system SHALL support flexible configuration.

**Details:**
- **FR-11.1:** Support YAML configuration files
- **FR-11.2:** Support environment variables
- **FR-11.3:** Allow per-application configuration
- **FR-11.4:** Support configuration validation
- **FR-11.5:** Provide configuration templates and examples
- **FR-11.6:** Support multiple environments (dev, staging, prod)

**Priority:** P1 (High)

