## 3. Non-Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Performance Requirements

| ID | Requirement | Target |
|----|-------------|--------|
| NFR-1 | Analysis completion time (P95) | < 3 minutes |
| NFR-2 | Quick health check (P95) | < 30 seconds |
| NFR-3 | API response time (P95) | < 500ms |
| NFR-4 | Data collection from New Relic | < 30 seconds |
| NFR-5 | Concurrent application analysis | Support 5+ apps |
| NFR-6 | System startup time | < 10 seconds |

### 3.2 Reliability Requirements

| ID | Requirement | Target |
|----|-------------|--------|
| NFR-7 | System availability | > 99.5% |
| NFR-8 | AI recommendation accuracy | > 85% |
| NFR-9 | Alert precision (true positive rate) | > 90% |
| NFR-10 | Graceful degradation on API failures | Continue with partial data |
| NFR-11 | Automatic retry on transient failures | 3 attempts with exponential backoff |

### 3.3 Scalability Requirements

| ID | Requirement | Target |
|----|-------------|--------|
| NFR-12 | Monitored applications | Support 50+ apps |
| NFR-13 | Concurrent analyses | 10+ parallel |
| NFR-14 | Historical data retention | 90 days |
| NFR-15 | Report storage | 1000+ reports |

### 3.4 Security Requirements

| ID | Requirement | Description |
|----|-------------|-------------|
| NFR-16 | API key management | Secure storage, never logged or committed |
| NFR-17 | Sensitive data sanitization | Remove passwords, API keys, PII before AI analysis |
| NFR-18 | Access control | Role-based access for different operations |
| NFR-19 | Audit logging | Log all analysis operations with user context |
| NFR-20 | Secure communication | HTTPS for all external API calls |
| NFR-21 | Secrets management | Support environment variables and secret managers |

### 3.5 Usability Requirements

| ID | Requirement | Description |
|----|-------------|-------------|
| NFR-22 | Setup time | < 30 minutes for initial setup |
| NFR-23 | Documentation | Comprehensive setup and usage guides |
| NFR-24 | Error messages | Clear, actionable error messages |
| NFR-25 | CLI usability | Intuitive commands with helpful feedback |
| NFR-26 | Report readability | Reports understandable by all engineers |

### 3.6 Maintainability Requirements

| ID | Requirement | Description |
|----|-------------|-------------|
| NFR-27 | Code coverage | > 70% test coverage |
| NFR-28 | Logging | Structured logging with appropriate levels |
| NFR-29 | Monitoring | Self-monitoring capabilities |
| NFR-30 | Modularity | Pluggable architecture for extensibility |
| NFR-31 | Documentation | Inline code documentation and architecture docs |

### 3.7 Operational Requirements

| ID | Requirement | Description |
|----|-------------|-------------|
| NFR-32 | Deployment | Support Docker containerization |
| NFR-33 | Resource usage | < 512MB memory, < 50% CPU (idle) |
| NFR-34 | Log management | Configurable log levels and rotation |
| NFR-35 | Health checks | Expose health check endpoints |
| NFR-36 | Graceful shutdown | Clean shutdown within 30 seconds |

### 3.8 Cost Requirements

| ID | Requirement | Target |
|----|-------------|--------|
| NFR-37 | OpenAI API cost per analysis | < $0.50 |
| NFR-38 | Total monthly operational cost | < $200 for 10 apps |
| NFR-39 | Cost optimization ROI | Identify 10x savings vs operational cost |

