### 3.5 Recommendation Generator

#### 3.5.1 Issue Identifier

```python
class IssueIdentifier:
    """
    Identifies and categorizes issues
    """
    
    def identify_root_cause(issue: Issue, context: ContextDocument) -> RootCause
    def assess_impact(issue: Issue) -> ImpactAssessment
    def find_related_issues(issue: Issue, all_issues: List[Issue]) -> List[Issue]
    def determine_urgency(issue: Issue) -> Urgency
```

**RootCause Model:**
```python
@dataclass
class RootCause:
    category: str  # "code", "configuration", "infrastructure", "external"
    description: str
    evidence: List[Evidence]
    confidence: float  # 0-1
    related_components: List[str]
    
@dataclass
class Evidence:
    type: str  # "metric", "log", "trace", "code"
    description: str
    data: Any
    timestamp: Optional[datetime]
```

#### 3.5.2 Solution Generator

```python
class SolutionGenerator:
    """
    Generates actionable solutions
    """
    
    def generate_code_fix(issue: Issue, code_context: CodeContext) -> CodeFix
    def suggest_configuration_change(issue: Issue) -> ConfigurationChange
    def recommend_infrastructure_adjustment(issue: Issue) -> InfrastructureChange
    def provide_best_practices(issue: Issue) -> List[BestPractice]
```

**Solution Models:**
```python
@dataclass
class CodeFix:
    file_path: str
    description: str
    diff: str  # Unified diff format
    before_code: str
    after_code: str
    line_numbers: Tuple[int, int]
    explanation: str
    confidence: float
    
@dataclass
class ConfigurationChange:
    config_file: str
    parameter: str
    current_value: Any
    recommended_value: Any
    reason: str
    expected_impact: str
    
@dataclass
class InfrastructureChange:
    component: str  # "database", "cache", "load_balancer", etc.
    change_type: str  # "scale_up", "scale_down", "add_resource", etc.
    details: str
    estimated_cost_impact: float
    expected_performance_improvement: str
```

