## 7. API Specifications

### 7.1 REST API Endpoints

```yaml
# Base URL: http://localhost:8000/api/v1

POST /analyze
  Description: Trigger analysis for an application
  Body:
    app_id: string
    time_range: optional<string>  # "1h", "24h", "7d"
    deep_dive: optional<bool>     # Force deep analysis
  Response:
    analysis_id: string
    status: string
    estimated_time: int  # seconds

GET /analyze/{analysis_id}
  Description: Get analysis results
  Response:
    analysis_id: string
    status: string  # "pending", "running", "completed", "failed"
    result: optional<AnalysisResult>
    progress: float  # 0-100

GET /health/{app_id}
  Description: Get current health score
  Response:
    app_id: string
    health_score: float
    status: string
    last_updated: datetime
    issues_count: int

GET /recommendations/{app_id}
  Description: Get latest recommendations
  Response:
    app_id: string
    recommendations: List[Recommendation]
    generated_at: datetime

POST /analyze/custom
  Description: Custom analysis with specific context
  Body:
    context: ContextDocument
    analysis_type: string  # "performance", "error", "cost"
  Response:
    result: AnalysisResult
```

### 7.2 CLI Interface

```bash
# Analyze application
ai-monitor analyze --app-id APP_ID [--deep-dive] [--output report.json]

# Continuous monitoring
ai-monitor monitor --app-id APP_ID --interval 60m

# Get health status
ai-monitor health --app-id APP_ID

# Run specific analysis type
ai-monitor analyze:performance --app-id APP_ID
ai-monitor analyze:errors --app-id APP_ID
ai-monitor analyze:cost --app-id APP_ID

# Generate report
ai-monitor report --app-id APP_ID --format markdown --output report.md

# Configuration
ai-monitor config --set new_relic.api_key=XXX
ai-monitor config --show
```

